      • calculateDifferencesAndAssignActions

        public void calculateDifferencesAndAssignActions(Deployment deployment)
        This method is the heart of the process of determining what will change in an environment as a result of a deployment. It works through all of the data and decides for each component what the difference is between what needs to be deployed and what is deployed. It probably looks scary but it is really only an implementation of a matrix. Each row of the matrix is listed in the if statement as a comment and the matrix is documented on Confluence in the multi-component deploy design.
        Parameters:
        deployment -
